"{\"uid\": \"news.cgtn.com-news-2024-08-23-Arshad-Nadeem-vows-to-continue-making-Pakistan-proud-after-Olympic-win-1whsu3X6vwA-p.html\", \"text\": \"Our Privacy Statement & Cookie Policy  By continuing to browse our site you agree to our use of cookies, revised Privacy Policy and Terms of Use. You can change your cookie settings through your browser.  Copied  Pakistan's star javelin thrower, Arshad Nadeem, received a hero's welcome upon returning home from the Paris Olympics. The 27-year-old was the first individual athlete to win a gold medal for Pakistan at the Summer Games. In an exclusive interview with CGTN, Nadeem vowed to continue making Pakistan proud with his exploits.  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466\"}"